<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malawi, Egypt Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and Malawi signed two
agreements on encouraging investment and promoting economic and
technical cooperation today during the visit of President Bakili
Muluzi of Malawi.
</P>
<P>
The agreements, the first between Egypt and the southeastern
African country in economic and technical fields, were signed after
a meeting between Egyptian Minister of state for Planning and
International Cooperation Zafer el-Beshri and Malawi Foreign
Minister Mapopa Chiapeta.
</P>
<P>
Under the first agreement, they agreed on setting up a joint
ministerial committee.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak held talks Sunday with Muluzi,
who wound up his three-day visit this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the Malawi delegation, which includes
ministers of foregin affairs, tourism and public works, held talks
with the Egyptian side that focused on promoting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The balance of trade between Egypt and Malawi stands at 40
million U.S. dollars in Malawi's favor. Egypt imports tea, tobacco
and meat from Malawi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
