<HEADLINE> Party Official Urges Public Servants to Do Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese public servants were
called today to adhere to the principle of serving the people
wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
All public servants, whatever they do and whatever position
they hold, must uphold and follow the goal of serving the people
wholeheartedly, and place the interests of the people above
everything, Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, said in a meeting with representatives of public
servants.
</P>
<P>
Public servants must resolutely implement the basic theory,
line and policies of the Party and make greater contributions to
the economic development and social progress of their respective
areas, thereby advancing the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
All public servants must use their power to serve the people
rather than to seek interests for themselves, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
"The greater the rights in your hands, the heavier the
responsibilities on your shoulders," he said, urging all public
servants to accept the supervision of the people and fight against
the abuse of rights.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged the public servants to resolutely trust and rely on
the masses, stay in close touch with the masses, heed the voice of
the masses, be concerned with their difficulties and do what they
expect.
</P>
<P>
Bad work style such as bureaucracy and formalism must be
prevented or eradicated, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
