<HEADLINE> DPRK Confirms Release of South Koreans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) today confirmed the release of two South
Koreans who had mistakenly crossed the Korean Military Demarcation
Line (MDL) into the DPRK four days ago.
</P>
<P>
The two were handed over to South Korea earlier today, the
DPRK's official KCNA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In Seoul, the South Korean media said that the two South
Koreans were released today by the army of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, said the United States Forces stationed in
South Korea (USFK).
</P>
<P>
At about ten o'clock in the morning, representatives of the
USFK and the Korean People's Army (KPA) met at the site of the
October-17 Demilitarized-Zone incident where the two South Koreans
were arrested.
</P>
<P>
During a joint investigation by USFK and KPA officials, the two
South Koreans said they "accidentally" crossed the Military
Demarcation Line in an area that was not clearly marked, into the
DPRK's side.
</P>
<P>
They were released four days after their detention, said the
USFK.
</P>
<P>
The two South Koreans, a 66-year-old woman and her 41 year-old
son, is in good physical condition and have returned to
Taesong-dong, a village south of the 4-kilometer-wide buffer zone
between the DPRK and South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971022.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder; "One Country, Two Systems" and China's Reunification (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fourth, adopting practical measures to promote exchanges
between the two sides. Jiang Zemin once said "we should pin our
hopes on the people of Taiwan." The great tradition of patriotism
of Taiwan people is an important force for developing relations
between the two sides and promoting peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Expanding exchanges will promote efforts to enhance mutual
understanding and achieve common views. Therefore efforts should
be made to increase trade and economic cooperation between the two
sides. Policies to encourage Taiwan investment in mainland areas
must be continued and the legal interests of Taiwan businesspeople
must be protected under all conditions.
</P>
<P>
It is important to expand exchanges and cooperation in the
science and technology sectors, as well as the cultural
sector. Related efforts will also promote the realization of
direct commercial, postal and transportation links.
</P>
<P>
People from all parties and circles in Taiwan, apart from a
small group of hardliners calling for "Taiwan Independence," are
welcome to exchange opinions on the reunification issue.
</P>
<P>
Fifth, adherance to the principle of "one country, two
systems". Following the reunification of the two sides, the
Chinese maiinland will continue to practise socialism, with Taiwan
retaining its capitalist system for a long period of time. Taiwan
will retain its social and economic systems, lifestyle and
nongovernmental relations with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan, a special administrative region following
reunification, will enjoy a high degree of autonomy, including
having its own legislature and administration of justice with the
right of final adjudication.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Taiwan can also have its own military force. The
central government will not send troops or public service people
to Taiwan. People from Taiwan will fill certain vacancies in the
central government leadership.
</P>
<P>
Finally, people from both sides share the same culture, and
should carry forward the fine tradition of the Chinese nation. The
small group of people in Taiwan who have attempted to sever
historic and cultural ties between the two sides are doomed to
failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
