<HEADLINE> UK Car Production at 20-Year High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Car production in Britain in the
first three quarters of this year was the highest for 20 years, at
1,247,299, which represents a 1.6 percent rise over the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
It will be most likely to make the industry's production for
the full year topping 1.7 million for the first time since the
early 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders
showed car production in September reaching 145,202, up 3.6
percent year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
Output for the domestic market was 7.1 percent higher, at
53,421; that for export was up 1.7 percent, at 90,232.
</P>
<P>
September's commercial vehicle production was also buoyant, the
23,072 units representing a year-on-year rise of 13.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Output for the UK market, at 10,984, was 10.6 percent higher;
that for export was up 20.8 percent, at 10,919. For the first
three quarters as a whole, output was up by the same percentage,
as cars at 177,091. 
</P>
</TEXT>
