<HEADLINE> UNESCO's 29th Meeting Opens in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Worldwide cooperation in the
fields of education, science, culture and communication is crucial
for mankind to fight poverty, hunger and illiteracy and establish
a true, long-lasting peace, a senior U.N. official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the 29th meeting of the
U.N. Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO),
UNESCO Director General Federico Mayor also welcomed Britain's
first presentation at the meeting since 1984.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, Britain and the United States declared to withdraw
UNESCO from and in July this year, the British government decided
to come back.
</P>
<P>
The biennial meeting brought together some 2,000
representatives of the organization's 186 member states. The
major topic of the meeting is to discuss the organization's
1998-99 draft budget and development program. 
