<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Rescuers have found bodies of
26 of the 30 people who went missing on Sunday after their ship
collided with a tugboat on the Barito river in Indonesia's central
Kalimantan province.
</P>
<P>
Authorities were trying to identify the bodies, a local
official was quoted as saying by reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
