<HEADLINE> Black Box of Indonesia's Ill-Fated Airbus Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The black box of Indonesia's
Garuda airbus a-300 which crashed near Medan, capital of North
Sumatra on September 26, was found today, TV Indonesia reported.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a Garuda official as saying that the black
box contains the entire conversation between the pilot and the
airport tower officials at the Polonian airport in Medan.
</P>
<P>
The accident, which killed all 234 people on board, is said to
be the worst in Indonesia's aviation history.
</P>
<P>
A search team, composed of representatives of the
transportation ministry, the armed forces and local people, has
been looking for the black box near the crash site for the past 25
days.
</P>
<P>
The black box will be sent to a foreign country for a check,
official sources said.  
