<HEADLINE> 2 Tonnes of Drug Seized in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Iranian armed policemen
confiscated 1,935 kilograms of opium in the southeastern province
of Kerman last week, Iran's official news Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The IRNA quoted Kerman Governor General Ali Panjalizadeh as
saying that following armed clashes, a number of drug traffickers
were killed and 131 others arrested. Four rifles were also seized.
</P>
<P>
Among the arrested are some notorious ring leaders engaged in
smuggling drugs into Iran via the southeastern border lines,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The territory of Iran has been used by mafia as the shortest
route for transit of narcotics from Afghanistan and Pakistan to
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Iran seized 185 tonnes of opium, 12 tonnes of morphine and 11
tonnes of heroin last year. 
</P>
