<HEADLINE> UN Supports Nyerere's Mediation in Burundi Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is
fully supporting Burundi peace talks mediated by former Tanzanian
president Julius Nyerere, a senior UN official told a press
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Victor Angelo, the UN Development Program (UNDP) resident
representative in Tanzania, said that he hoped something tangible
would come out of the wisdom and talents of Nyerere, a well-known
politician in Africa.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the world body is still committed to ensure
that all the environmental damages caused by the refugees from
Rwanda and Burundi in Tanzania would be rehabilitated by the UN
substantial economic aid.
</P>
<P>
Angelo warned that if favorable measures were not taken, the
regions, where thousand of refugees are felling trees for both
domestic use and farming, are likely to experience harsh climate
in the future.
</P>
<P>
"These regions are badly affected and most of the rivers are
dry," he said, adding that the residents in the regions are now
witnessing water shortage. 
</P>
