<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-21 19:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Urges Israel, PNA to Create Peace Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
Mideast peace envoy Miguel Moratinos today urged Israel and the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to create a peace mechanism
in a bid to prevent new crisis in the Israeli-Palestinian peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos told Israel Radio that the current situation in the
region is much better than that of a few weeks ago, when the peace
talks between Israelis and Palestinians mired in a crisis after
two suicide bombing attacks took place in Jerusalem in July and
September.
</P>
<P>
A total of 25 people, including five suicide bombers were
killed and more than 300 injured in the bombing attacks.
</P>
<P>
He said he is optimistic about the progress in the peace
negotiations between Israel and the PNA, which were resumed early
this month after a seven-month-long deadlock and will continue in
Washington next week.
</P>
<P>
The envoy called for Israel and the PNA to "take profit of this
peaceful moment to create a mechanism and institute an
international framework in order that we will not go back to the
same situation that we were unfortunately facing during last
month."
</P>
<P>
Referring to the mechanism, EU has proposed that Israel and the
PNA adopt a code of conduct, which was described by Moratinos as a
framework for final-status talks.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos confirmed that the code proposal, that calls for
safeguarding all the signed agreements in the peace process and
for introducing confidence-building measures to bolster the fight
against terrorism and refrain from activities harmful to the
progress, has won positive responses from Israel and PNA.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai Tuesday morning, the envoy also raised the issue of a
permanent security committee as a part of the code, which would
consist of Israelis and Palestinians and could include EU and the
United States representatives if the two parties agreed.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos said that the establishment of the committee is aimed
at boosting international cooperation in the region to fight
terrorism and avoid violence in a permanent basis.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the possibility of the resumption of
Israeli-Syrian peace talks, Moratinos said more work is needed.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Syrian process was stalled in March last year after
a series of bombing attacks against Israelis by Muslim
extremists. Syria conditions peace talks on an Israeli promise of
total withdrawal of troops from the occupied Golan Heights.
</P>
</TEXT>
