<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Basic Law and the
"one country, two systems" principle have been fully implemented
since the island was returned to China on July 1, Hong Kong chief
Tung Chee Hwa said here today.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive of China's Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region made the remark at a reception given in his honor by
Chinese Ambassador to Britain Ma Zhengang this evening.
</P>
<P>
"On July 1 Hong Kong was reunited with China and we began a new
era in Hong Kong," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"Since then, the fundamental elements outlined by the Basic Law
and the 'one country, two systems' concept have been fully
implemented," he stressed. "Life in Hong Kong goes on as well," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive said that with the return of Hong Kong, the
Sino-British relationship will turn to a new and glorious page and
Hong Kong will be a bridge for improving the relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
In his toast, the Chinese ambassador said that continued
prosperity, stability and development in Hong Kong is the common
aspiration of the people the world over, and what happened in the
past 112 days in Hong Kong has fully lived up to those
expectations.
</P>
<P>
"All the successes should be attributed to the Chinese
government's determination to carry out to the full the principles
of 'one country, two systems', 'Hong Kong people administering
Hong Kong' and 'a high degree of autonomy', to strenuous efforts
of the 6.5 million people of Hong Kong, and to the able and
brilliant leadership of Mr.Tung Chee Hwa and his colleagues," Ma
said
</P>
<P>
The reception was attended by over 100 guests, including former
British prime minister Margaret Thatcher and British minister of
state for foreign affairs Derek Fatchett.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa arrived in London this morning following talks in
Brussels with senior European Commissionn officials. 
