minister that his company, which exported 1,300 tons of sugar to
Rwanda last year, welcomes the opportunity to export sugar to
Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Deputy Transport and Communication Minister Gilbert
Mulululu urged Zambian businessmen not to wait for the government
to organize a trip to Rwanda for them but should instead start on
their own.
</P>
<P>
During the tour of the cement works, Zambian Deputy Commerce
Minister Jazzman Chikwakwa said that the economy of Zambia lays
in the hands of the private sector that is why the government has
moved away from dictating to them what to do.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister appealed industries to move with the times
by constantly acquiring new technology and rehabilitating the old
equipment instead of blaming the government.
</P>
<P>
Zambia has exported 1,000 tons of cement to Rwanda this year
and is looking forward for more business opportunities with it.
</P>
