<HEADLINE> Tourism Booms in Cyprus, Minister Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus has achieved a unique
and remarkable success in tourism in the last two decades, tourism
minister said today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Cyprus received 2 million foreign tourists, doubling
the number a decade ago, Kyriacos Christofi told a World Tourism
Organization meeting in Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
The industry earned 1.5 billion U.S. dollars last year,
accounting for 20 percent of Cyprus' gross domestic product of the
year,
</P>
