<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Xiaolangdi Dam Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Xiaolangdi Multipurpose
Dam, the largest project of its kind ever built on the Yellow
River, China's second largest river, will be completed on October
28.
</P>
<P>
The damming process includes four phases.
</P>
<P>
The first phase, which commenced on September 25 and will be
completed on October 14, required the dumping of 210,000 cubic
meters of stone into the river in order to narrow the water
channel to a width of 106 meters.
</P>
<P>
The second phase, which commenced on October 19, included the
dismantling of two cofferdams, one upstream and the other
downstream.
</P>
<P>
The third phase, which will be completed in 40 hours between
October 26-28, will involve dumping 90,000 cu.m. of stone into the
river at a rate of 2,280 cu.m. per hour.
</P>
<P>
The fourth phase will involve filling the stone dam with sand
and gravel in order to raise the height of the dam to 143
meters. Some 160,000 cu.m. of stone and earth will be handled in a
period of 120 hours.
</P>
<P>
Damming the river is a challenging due to the rapid current at
the mouth of the dam. The average flow rate in the section is 7.05
meters per second, according to Cao Zhengqi, chief engineer of the
project.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the water level between upstream and the downstream
will drop by as much as 3.2 meters, Cao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
