<HEADLINE> Italy Grants HKSAR Passport holders Multiple-entry Visas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) today welcomed the Italian
government's announcement that HKSAR passport holders may be
granted multiple-entry Schengen visas valid for up to five years.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made through the Consulate General of
Italy in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A HKSAR government spokesman said: "This announcement, similar
to a recent move by Germany to grant multiple-entry visas,
reflects a growing confidence amongst European Union member states
in the SAR passport and in its holders traveling to Europe."
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR government continues to welcome Italian
nationals to visit Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the spokesman announced that the Republic of
Cape Verde, an African nation, has agreed to grant visa-free
access to HKSAR passport holders.
</P>
<P>
"This will enable HKSAR passport holders to visit and stay in
Cape Verde without a visa for up to one month," he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the arrangement will help promote trade,
business and tourism links between Hong Kong and Cape Verde.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister of Cape Verde Carlos Veiga, who is on a visit to
China, and his Chinese counterpart Li Peng noted and welcomed this
development at their meeting in Beijing today.  
</P>
