<HEADLINE> China Disciplines Another Corrupt Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Chang Zheng, vice-chairman of
the Guizhou Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, is yet another corrupt official uncovered
during China's intensive anti-corruption campaign.
</P>
<P>
The Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Ministry of Supervision
revealed that Chang has been charged with abuse of power and
accepting bribes totalling 70,000 yuan from a local real estate
company.
</P>
<P>
Chang accepted what he referred to as a "token of gratitude"
after pressuring the Guizhou Daily Newspaper to invest four
million yuan in the Wanbang Real Estate Development Co. Limited.
</P>
<P>
Chang has been relieved of all official duties and will be
expelled from the Communist Party of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
