<HEADLINE> New Health Minister Appointed in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Health Minister
Anwar Al-Nouri resigned today for "personal reasons" and his
successor was announced.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Salem Al-Sabah accepted Al-Noori's resignation and appointed
Adel Khaled Al-Sebeih to replace him, according to Kuwait News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Al-Noori took the health portfolio in a new cabinet after
National Assembly elections in October 1996. He was reportedly to
have offered resignation several times during the past year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts and observers foresaw a reshuffle by Sheikh Saad of
his cabinet aimed at ushering a new era of politics after he
returned back from a seven-month recuperation abroad following a
colon surgery in March.
</P>
<P>
In a televised speech delivered during a Cabinet session
Sunday, Sheikh Saad said ministers should work harder to implement
reform on issues such as citizenship, housing, education, health
and population. 
