<HEADLINE> Trade Fair Reports Large Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Export contracts reached 3.2
billion US dollars for the first seven days of the 82nd China
Export Commodities Fair in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented a 4.1 percent rise on last year's fair,
according to the organizer.
</P>
<P>
A further breakdown shows that the transaction value for light
industrial products totaled 978 million US dollars, with contracts
for electronics and textiles hitting 898 million US dollars and
715 million US dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
The total value of contracts for foodstuffs, local produce,
livestock products, minerals and chemicals dropped from the
previous year's figure.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which opened on Oct. 15, attracted 35,310
businesspeople from 149 countries and regions, up 5.21 percent on
the 1996 fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
