<HEADLINE> Bank Loans For Hydropower Station Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank
signed a contract today to grant loans totalling 4.26 billion yuan
for the construction of a hydropower station in southwest China's
Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dachaoshan Hydropower Station, a key state project which
will be the largest power station of its kind in the province,
will have an installed generating capacity of 1.35 million kw.
</P>
<P>
The station's first 225,000 kw generator will go online in 2001.
</P>
<P>
A shareholding company, the first of its kind in the country,
has been established to construct the power station.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Bank has agreed to provide loans of over
17 billion yuan for 61 projects in the province, with loans of 1.2
billion yuan already granted thus far.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the hydropower station, the largest project the
bank has funded in Yunnan, is expected to promote economic growth
in both the province and the southwest region. 
</P>
