<HEADLINE> India Develops New Pressure Sensitive Adhesive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 22 (Xinhua)-- Indian researchers at the
Sriram Institute of Industrial Research (SRI) here have developed
a technology for producing non-toxic pressure sensitive adhesives
for use in medical applications, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The adhesives have been further used to prepare microporous
adhesive tapes and surgical drapes.
</P>
<P>
During surgery, disinfection is now possible by using
paper-tissue based surgical drape which prevents body fluids from
coming in contact with skin. It absorbs blood and other body
fluids, preventing further spilling on the surface.  
