<HEADLINE> Portugal to Renew New Coop Ties With Angola: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres has said Portugal would like to become a
strategic partner of Angola and to develop a new type of economic
and business cooperation relationship with the country.
</P>
<P>
He said Angola will become Portugal's precedent cooperative
partner in the process of achieving its economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks here on Tuesday while speaking at the
Angola Investment Forum.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said the new bilateral cooperative relationship that
is expected to be set up should make a feature of two-way
pattern.
</P>
<P>
That means that Portuguese can invest in Angola while Angolans
can do the same in Portugal and the two countries can also
cooperate with each other in the third market, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Guterres pointed out that the two countries should develop
strategic partnership in a bid to make greater achievement in
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should open up long-term cooperation,
instead of taking it as an expedient measure, he further noted.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said Portugal hopes to clear away obstacles that
hinder the bilateral cooperation in order to make a new start for
the cooperative relationship of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He called on entrepreneurs of the two countries to participate
in the bilateral cooperative activities and act in concert to
make more fortunes for the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Guterres arrived here Monday for a five-day visit. Top on the
agenda of his first visit to Angola is to step up the economic
cooperation between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
