<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Lowers Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank announced
today that interest rates on bank loans and deposits will be
lowered effective tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Interest rates on deposits and loans will be reduced by an
average 1.1 and 1.5 percentage points respectively, according to
the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of reductions in interest rates, which follow
similar across-the-board reductions in May and August last year,
is in response to declining prices and is designed to lower
interest costs for enterprises, support the reform of state-owned
enterprises, and promote sustained, rapid and sound national
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Beginning tomorrow, the benchmark annual interest rate on
one-year term deposits will be reduced from 7.47 percent to 5.67
percent, with the annual interest rate on demand deposits dropping
from 1.98 percent to 1.71 percent.
</P>
<P>
Annual interest rates for term deposits following the latest
readjustments will include: 5.94 percent for two-year fixed
deposits, down from 7.92 percent; 6.21 percent for three-year term
deposits, down from 8.28 percent; and 6.66 percent for five-year
term deposits, down from nine percent.
</P>
<P>
Annual interest rates on loans will include: 7.65 percent for
short-term loans of less than six months, down from 9.18 percent;
8.64 percent for loans between six months to one year, down from
10.08 percent; 9.36 percent for loans of one to three years, down
from 10.98 percent; 9.9 percent for loans of three to five years,
down from 11.7 percent; and 10.53 percent for loans of over five
years, down from 12.42 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
