<HEADLINE> China's First Solely-Owned German Enterprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Ipsen Industrial Boiler
(Shanghai) Co., the first solely-owned German company in China
founded by the Ipsen International GmbH, has gone into operation
in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
The company, set up in the Minhang District at an estimated
cost of 14 million US dollars, is mainly involved in heat
treatment and processing. The company will provide heat treatment
facilities for automobile, cutting tools and machine-building
industries in China and Asia-Pacific markets.
</P>
<P>
Ipsen has sold more than 100 sets of heat treatment facilities
in China.  
</P>
