<HEADLINE> Asian Business Cities Discuss Market Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 30 delegates from
nine of Asia's top business cities gathered here today at the
annual meetings of the Business Partner City (BPC) Network to
discuss market opportunities and information exchanges within the
region.
</P>
<P>
Raymond Yip, senior manager for trade promotion of the Hong
Kong Trade Development Council, described the meetings as an
extremely auspicious event, as well as an important opportunity to
strengthen trade links among these cities.
</P>
<P>
"All the BPC delegates have an ideal opportunity to see for
themselves how well the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of
China is functioning after its first 100 days under the unique
'one country, two systems' principle," Yip said.
</P>
<P>
He said these meetings demonstrate the continued confidence of
these cities in Hong Kong's future as a regional business hub and
as a priority partner for trade and commerce.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by Osaka, the BPC Network is an alliance of trade
promotional and municipal organizations from the Asia-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong was the first city to join Osaka in the network in
1988. Also in the network are Singapore, Bangkok, Kuala Lumpur,
Manila, Jakarta, Seoul, Shanghai and Ho Chi Minh City.  
