<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Project Open To Different Suppliers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The giant Three Gorges
Hydro-electric Power Project has been opened to both Chinese and
foreign suppliers, in a move to reduce costs and guarantee
quality, according to officials in charge of the project.
</P>
<P>
The China Three Gorges Development Corporation has decided to
allow competition among material and equipment suppliers. Deputy
General Manager Qin Zhongyi told Xinhua that 10 million tons of
steel, timber, cement, coal ash, oil and explosives are needed,
accounting for about 40 percent of the total cost.
</P>
<P>
And billions of yuan will be spent on generators and machinery.
</P>
<P>
To ensure quality and cost, the corporation plans to begin
purchasing all materials and equipment from both local and
international suppliers after the river-blocking, which is the
start of the second phase of the project, Qin said.
</P>
<P>
An equipment exhibition center has been built for this, which
will serve as a permanent market-place for suppliers to show their
goods. On Tuesday, a materials and equipment exhibition opened at
the center, attracting suppliers from the United States, Germany,
France, Sweden, Japan, Finland, Singapore and other
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
