<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Rebound Sharply in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in Tokyo rebounded
sharply today, following the overnight surge in New York.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected stocks on the First Section
at the Tokyo Stock Exchange closed at 17,687.61, up 477.52 points,
or 2.77 percent, from Tuesday's end.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, advanced 22.42 points, or 1.67
percent, to 1,366.74.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the First Section came to an estimated 430 million
shares, up from Tuesday's 332.02 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Stock prices bounced back for the first time in four trading
days on brisk gains on Wall Street, where the Dow Jones Industrial
Average ended above the 8,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
On the Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar remained fettered in a
narrow range in the upper 120 yen level.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was changing hands at 120.76-78 yen at 5 p.m. local
time, down from 120.80-83 yen at 9 a.m., and from 120.90-121.00
yen late Tuesday in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
