<HEADLINE> Helping Hand for Typhoon-Struck Parts Of East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Five military vehicles
carrying 5,000 items of cotton clothing went to disaster-struck
counties in east China's Zhejiang one cold autumn morning recently.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to provide local victims with enough food, warm
clothing, and shelter before winter sets in," a provincial
official explains.
</P>
<P>
A violent typhoon hit the coastal province in August, leaving
more than 10 million people with losses, and 170,000 buildings
destroyed. Losses were put at more than 26 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Provincial Civil Affair departments have allocated
more than 45 million yuan for disaster relief. Building materials
have also been sent to the disaster area to help with the
rebuilding of homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
