<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- A top FIFA official encouraged
Australia to bid for the 2010 World Cup finals, according to
reports reaching here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sepp Blatter, secretary general of the world soccer ruling body
who is inspecting Adelaide's Hindmarsh Stadium, rated Australia as
"a logical candidate" for the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
"Have a look at 2010. You are a young country and have young
people here," he was quoted as saying. 
