<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
again on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 39.54 points to close at 1731.68
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 256.83 million units,
valued at 602.35 million Singapore dollars (about 381.23 million
U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 366 to 29 while
209 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Land was the most
actively traded stock as it registered a turnover of 15.85 million
shares. It was followed by the Hong Kong Land which had 13.39
million shares traded. RHB Capital Warrant99 saw 7.77 million
units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the 29 gainers
of the day as it rose by 3.6 dollars to finish at 39 Singapore
dollars. Asean Fund increased by 1.5 dollars to end at 12 U.S.
dollars while IPCO was 15 cents higher to close at 2.35 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Hong Leong Industry was the biggest loser as
it declined by 1.12 dollars to close at 2.88 Singapore dollars.
Bukit Sembawang fell by 90 cents to end at 17 Singapore dollars.
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) finished 80 cents lower at 15
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
