<HEADLINE> Film On Opium War To Be Shown In Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The well-known Chinese
director Xie Jing went to Taiwan today to attend the debut of his
epic work "The Opium War".
</P>
<P>
This is the first inland area film to be shown in Taiwan since
a copyright agreement was signed.
</P>
<P>
The film was a hit in China soon after it was released in June
and has had more than 70 million yuan in box-office revenues. In
Shanghai, 2.13 million people have seen the film, giving a record
14 million yuan in revenues. It has also been well received in
Hong Kong and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Xie said that several of his films have been shown in Taiwan,
but most were videos, and he expressed his appreciation for the
Central Motion Picture Corporation's help in introducing his film
to the island.
</P>
<P>
Some actors and actresses who appear in the film accompanied
Xie today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
