<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Holds '97 International AV Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 70 international
exhibitors are displaying their latest audio-visual products at
the Hong Kong International Audio Visual Show '97, which was
opened here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Centering around the theme "Close Encounter with Multimedia",
this year's show features leading international brands. On display
are digital video camera, domestic multi-media theater system,
Internet services, photographic and other related multi-media
components.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong is a major market and producer of films and AV
equipment in the world, AV show has become an annual event in this
special administrative region of China.
</P>
<P>
Last year Hong Kong exported 113 billion HK dollars (14.49
billion US dollars) worth of audio-visual products. At the same
time it imported 133 billion HK dollars (17.05 billion US dollars)
 worth of these products.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, Hong Kong's exports of
photographic apparatus and equipment reached 7.5 billion HK
dollars (0.96 billion US dollars), up nine percent from the same
period last year, while the imports of such products jumped 11
percent to 6.9 billion HK dollars (0.88 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The five-day show will last till October 26.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
