<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Railway Project Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- A major railway project in
China's Guangdong province, linking Guangzhou, the provincial
capital, with Zhuhai, a special economic zone near Macao, began
today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua and Vice-Chairman of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference National Committee Ye
Xuanping attended an opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Benhui, deputy mayor of Zhuhai, said that the 142-km
railway will cost 8.4 billion yuan and is scheduled for completion
within four years.
</P>
<P>
It will be a joint project with 80 percent of the funds coming
from Zhuhai investors.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of the city's efforts to improve its
infrastructure and links with other parts of the country. Work on
Zhuhai Airport and Zhuhai Port is also part of this
planning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
