<HEADLINE> Angola Hopes to Enhance Cooperation with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Prime Minister Franca
Van-Dunem today expressed the hope that cooperation between
Angola and China be enhanced and expanded.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks here during a meeting with Yang Wensheng,
assistant to the Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC) who is currently visiting Angola.
</P>
<P>
Van-Dunem said, the two countries have enjoyed good
cooperative relations for a long time. Angola is undergoing a
period of peace consolidation and economic rehabilitation at the
moment and needs to cooperate with China in many areas, he added.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister thanked China for its support to Angola in
the United Nations. He expressed the hope that the two countries
would further enhance cooperation in the international sphere and
bilateral economies.
</P>
<P>
Yang Wensheng expressed thanks to Angola for its support on
the human right issue. He also briefed the prime minister on the
current economic cooperation between the two countries, adding
that China would seek for a new mode to boost cooperation between
enterprises of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Yang arrived in Angola on October 19. During his visit, he
also met with Angolan Foreign Minister Venancio De Moura, who
reiterated the country's "One China" stand and urged China to
take realistic measures to contain Taiwan's attempt in expanding
its influence in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
