<HEADLINE> HK, Japanese Stock Exchange Companies Reach Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Hong
Kong (SEHK) and Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE) of Japan have reached
an agreement on sharing market information, initiating a formal
avenue of communication between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Henry Law, spokesman for the SEHK, told reporters earlier this
morning that the accord was signed Tuesday and denied any
connection of the move with the current rises and falls at Hong
Kong's stock market.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will enable the SEHK and the TSE to have access
to each other's market surveillance information as may be required
for the purpose of detecting or preventing possible manipulative
activities involving both markets, he said.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing the market interrelationship between the SEHK and
the TSE, the spokesman stressed that sharing certain market
information may help maintain the integrity of both markets.
</P>
</TEXT>
