<DOCNO> XIE19971022.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto: Counter-Trade Could Help Solve Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
said here today that counter-trading could help solve various
economic challenges such as fierce competition, capital limitation
and supply of raw materials.
</P>
<P>
"Indonesia has a number of experiences in counter-trading, both
government-to-government and inter-private sectors," the president
said at the opening of the Asia-Pacific Counter-Trade Association
conference.
</P>
<P>
He said the system could bring in enormous benefits, among
which are the opening of new markets, assurance of supply and
financial support for raw materials, capital goods purchase and
the creation of a financial mechanism that can boost inter-state
direct trade relations.
</P>
<P>
The counter-trade system could also facilitate the transfer of
technology and the increase of investment, he added.
</P>
<P>
The counter-trade/counter-purchase system is a kind of barter
in the world market by bilateral or multilateral transaction in
the lack of foreign currency between the buyer and the seller.
</P>
<P>
A total of 175 participants from 24 countries are attending the
conference which will last till Friday.
</P>
<P>
The event is organized by the Asia Pacific Counter-Trade
Association, a Singapore-based nonprofit organization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
