<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> VW Sales Rise 8.9 Percent Through September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Volkswagen car group today
reported its sales increased by 8.9 percent, or 270,000 cars, to over
3.2 million in the first nine months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Europe's largest car maker currently accounted for over 10
percent share of the world market, it said in a statement issued from
headquarters in Wolfsburg.
</P>
<P>
The group's Skoda cars, made in the Czech Republic, registered a
28.7 percent growth in sales during the period, while the sales of
Audi and the Spanish-made Seat were up 14 percent, followed by VW
cars, up 4.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
In European market, sales rose 7.5 percent to 2.1 million cars,
while those in North America rose 10.1 percent to about 200,000. VW
group sold 602,000 cars in South America and Africa, up 7.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the Asia-Pacific region, sales surged by 16.4 percent to 290,000
cars, including 213,000 cars in China alone, an increase of 20
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
