<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Checks On Health Care Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Health departments of central
China's Henan province have taken steps to improve the
certification system for health care products.
</P>
<P>
Health care products have developed rapidly in China in recent
years, and more than 2,100 factories now produce 3,387 health care
items in China.
</P>
<P>
Growth in the sector has also meant the cropping up of major
problems, which include listing drugs as health care products and
using some new medicines both for medical treatment and for health
care.
</P>
<P>
So, to get its health care house in order, the province will
ban the production, sale, and use of non-health care products, and
ask factories, even those whose products have been approved, to
hand over samples to the Health Ministry for a second round of
approval.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
