<HEADLINE> China Sets Date For Damming Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Yellow River, the second
largest in China, is scheduled for blocking on October 28 to
prepare for work on the multi-billion yuan Xiaolangdi Hydropower
Project in Luoyang, Henan province.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made on Tuesday at a meeting on the project,
presided over by Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
The project is meant to control the Yellow River, where the bed
has been rising because of the large amount of sand brought down
from the upper reaches that pass through the severely eroded Loess
Plateau, and to generate electricity.
</P>
<P>
The project began in October 1994. 
</P>
