<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan's Oil, Natural Gas to Be Further Developed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- There are bright prospects in
the development of oil and natural gas industries in Kazakhstan,
Kuandykov Baltabek, chief executive of the National Petroleum and
Natural Gas Company, said today.
</P>
<P>
This year's output of petroleum of Kazakhstan is expected to
reach 26 million tons, an increase of 3 million tons above last
year, said Baltabek at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan has introduced from abroad a big amount of funds and
imported advanced technology and equipment for oil development,
said Kuandykov, whose predecessor Nurlan Balgimbaev was appointed
as prime minister of the oil-rich central Asian country earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan is boosting cooperation with major petroleum
businesses from China, Russia, Iran, the United States and Italy,
said Baltabek.
</P>
<P>
He told the press that agreements on cooperating with foreign
countries in developing natural gas in Kalachaganak and oil and
natural gas in the continental shelf of the Caspian Sea are
expected to be finalized in November.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan has been proved to have over 2.1 billion tons of oil
reserves and 1,797 billion cubic meters of natural gas reserves.
</P>
</TEXT>
