<HEADLINE> Two Asian Records Fall on Track of National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Two Asian records cracked in
the women's 200 meters and 400m hurdles at the Eighth National
Games here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sprinter Li Xuemei claimed the 200m national title with an
Asian mark of 22.01 seconds, breaking the previous record of 22.39
set by Susanthika Jayasinghe of Sri Lankan in the World Athletics
Championships in Athens in August.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Liu Xiaomei also surpassed the Asian record by
clocking 22.36 for the second place.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Limei of Guangxi won the 400m hurdles title with another
Asian mark of 53.38 seconds, slicing 0.58 seconds off the previous
mark of 53.96, which was established by her compatriot Han Qing in
1993.
</P>
<P>
Early in the National Games, Li Xuemei took the 100m title by
breaking the Asian mark twice. She first timed in 10.90 seconds
in the heats and later claimed the natioanl title in 10.79
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The women's 100m and 200m world records were all held by
Florence Griffith Joyner of the United States in 10.49 and 21.34
seconds respectively.
</P>
<P>
Li, 20, failed to leave her presence on the podium at the
Athens Worlds, but she said she could have performed much better
there.
</P>
<P>
"That's my first time to take part in an international meet,"
she said. "I felt very nervous to compete along with so many big
names."
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe emerged as Asia's top women spinter by winning the
silver in the 200m event in Athens. But Li is confident now that
she can overtake the Sri Lankan for the honour.
</P>
<P>
"I belive I can beat her in the Asian Games in Thailand next
year," she said.
</P>
<P>
Lang Yinglai of Liaoning, a new protege of Ma Junren, grabbed
the gold in the women's 800 meters by clocking 1:57.62. Chen
Xuehui of Guangxi finished second with 0.20 seconds behind and Lin
Na, also from Liaoning, ranked third in 1:58.16.
</P>
<P>
Chen expressed her great thanks to coach Ma, saying that
"without coach Ma's unique training, I could never win a gold and
I will definitely make more progresses under his charge."
</P>
<P>
"It is not too bad to take the gold without a record time from
the 800m event as it is not our strong event for these young
runners," said Ma.
</P>
<P>
The coach explained that both Lin and Lang suffered injuries in
their ankles.
</P>
<P>
"It's a hard victory. I extend my congratulations to them," Ma
said, sitting at the first row of the stand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
