<HEADLINE> Booming Foreign Trade in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
province continues opening wider to the outside world and its
foreign trade has increased by an annual 13.5 percent in recent
years, says a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
During the 1993-96 period, foreign trade was worth 6.641
billion US dollars, 4.76 billion US dollars of which was for
exports.
</P>
<P>
The province exports more than 10,000 products to 130 countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have paid attention to structural adjustments
in exports, increasing the proportion of mechanical products and
textiles from 83.2 percent in 1992 to 87.6 percent last year,
while decreasing exports of agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, 1,547 overseas-funded projects have been launched,
involving 1.64 billion US dollars in overseas funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
