<HEADLINE> Processing Business In Tianjin Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports in the
processing business in Tianjin, the largest port city in north
China, hit a record four billion US dollars in the first three
quarters of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents a year-on-year increase of 15.9 percent,
2.1 billion US dollars in exports and 1.8 billion US dollars in
imports, according to the customs office.
</P>
<P>
Solely foreign-funded enterprises accounted for more than 50
percent of that amount. Goods with a high added value, and goods
from private enterprises have begun to account for a larger part
of the foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Authorities say the improvement comes from the investment
environment and a series of preferential policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
