<HEADLINE> Rizhao-Pusan Container Route Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- A container shipping route has
been opened linking Rizhao in east China's Shandong Province with
Pusan of the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
Opened October 16, it is the 51st international shipping route
launched by Rizhao and will transport food and aquatic products,
textiles from Shandong and neighboring cities to the ROK, and sundry
goods from the ROK to China.
</P>
<P>
Located on the Yellow Sea, Rizhao Port is one of the 10 largest
in China, with an annual handling capacity of 17 million tons.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 ROK enterprises have set up firms in Jinan,
capital of Shandong province, and the city will participate in a
December trade fair in Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
