<HEADLINE> Uganda Urges Kenya to Remove Trade Obstacles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has called on Kenya to
remove all major trade obstacles between the two countries which
are heavily biased in favour of Kenya, the local newspaper The
People reported today.
</P>
<P>
Recent official statistics show that Kenya exported goods
worth 184 million U.S. dollars to Uganda in 1995/96 while the
latter's exports to Kenya were a mere 19 million dollars in the
same period.
</P>
<P>
However, the 19-million-dollar exports include tea, one of
Uganda major exports, which is auctioned in Mombasa, a port city
in Kenya, but does not end up in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The paper said unfavorable bureaucracy frustrated Ugandan
exporters through cumbersome licensing, road block, gratuity
demands at road-blocks and imprisonment of Ugandans on genuine
business trips. 
</P>
</TEXT>
