<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diversion Project Put into Use at Xiaolangdi on Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The main course of the
Yellow River was diverted into the diversion tunnel at Xiaolangdi
in central China's Henan province on Tuesday when a 3-meter-wide
gap was made in an upstream cofferdam.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, the water flowed from the tunnel into a channel
filled with water on Monday when a downstream cofferdam was
dismantled.
</P>
<P>
The combined flow then entered an energy-consumption pool before
running farther downstream into the river's main course.
</P>
<P>
The upstream cofferdam, constructed of 35,000 cubic meters of
earth and stone, should be removed by October 25.
</P>
<P>
The river will be dammed on October 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
