<HEADLINE> German Consulting Company Opens China Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest management
consultant opened a branch recently in the Pudong New Area of
Shanghai, China's industrial center.
</P>
<P>
Roland Berger &AMP; Partners's Asia manager says the company has
the idea of developing this potential market, as the country
increases efforts to reform its state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
China's economic development creates a need for management
expertise and development strategies. The German company's annual
business in China has grown from 9 percent of its total in 1995 to
the present 14 percent, and is expected to grow to 30-40 percent
in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
The field of consulting in China is at an early stage. There
are some 400 businesses, doing 30 to 40 million US dollars in
business annually, mainly at a rudimentary level, with information
gathering, market surveys, and investment advice.
</P>
<P>
Roland Berger has more than 30 branches and offices around the
world, and nearly 700 consultants. It did 413 million Deutschmarks
in business last year, putting it first in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch will provide consulting services for
Chinese enterprises in the area of acquisition, reorganization,
modern enterprise system, development strategies, and marketing
plans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
