<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Experiment with Modern Enterprise System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
industrial center, is working on an economic master plan to
establish a framework for a modern enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Xu Kuangdi said at a conference recently attended by
managers of the city's industrial firms that the city's goals are to
liminate inferior systems while encouraging the development of
superior systems, retain and increase the value of state
assets, establish a system of free choice for workers, and
select the best workers through competition.
</P>
<P>
The master plan will also encourage the development of new
products, technological transformation, expanded market share and
improved economic efficiency, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will also increase competition among enterprises,
speed up high-tech development and upgrade technology in key
industries.
</P>
<P>
State enterprises in the fields of iron and steel,
petrochemicals, telecommunications, micro-electronics,
pharmaceuticals and others will be re-organized to make the best
use of assets, technology and technical personnel.
</P>
<P>
Diversifying ownership, expediting mergers of small
enterprises, leasing and introducing a system of contracts are
necessary reform measures, Xu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
