<HEADLINE> Fujian Tightens Export Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's coastal Fujian
Province will tighten controls on export commodity licenses to
ensure their quality.
</P>
<P>
The move will affect 11 categories of goods including
machinery, electronics, pottery, cotton, coal, toys, motor
vehicles and animal husbandry products, according to an official
of the provincial commodity inspection office.
</P>
<P>
To date, Fujian has issued 254 export commodity quality
licenses to be presented on inspection. However, quality remains a
persistent problem.
</P>
<P>
Stricter quality control on export commodities will enhance the
competitiveness of Fujian's products in the international market,
the official said.  
