<HEADLINE> Chinese Li Xuemei Betters 200m Asian Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese women sprinter Li
Xuemei claimed the 200-meter national title with an Asian mark at
the Eighth National Games here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Li clocked 22.01 seconds to better the Asian
mark of 22.39 set by a Sri Lankan woman in the World Athletics
Championships in Athens this year.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Liu Xiaomei also surpassed the Asian mark by
clocking 22.36 for the second place.
</P>
<P>
Early in the National Games, Li took the 100-meter title by
breaking the Asian mark twice. She first timed in 10.90 seconds
in the heats and later claimed the natioanl title in 10.79
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The women's 100m and 200m world records were all held by
Florence Griffith Joyner of the United States in 10.49 and 21.34
seconds respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
