<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organisation of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim arrived in
Zimbabwe on Tuesday to attend the chiefs of defence staff meeting
on Africa's peace-keeping missions which will open here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to journalists on arrival, Salim said the meeting
comes at the right time when the continent meets with some
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting will allow the defence chiefs to exchange
ideas and come up with peacekeeping initiatives.
</P>
<P>
''Africa must resume its own responsibilities in conflict
resolution because if it does not the international community
will not help,'' said Salim.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting will focus on the continent's present
and future peacekeeping initiatives since the launch in 1993 by
OAU of the Mechanism For Conflict Prevention, Management and
Resolution in Africa.
</P>
<P>
On the Congo crisis, Salim had told ''The Herald'' news paper
that the OAU and the international community at large failed to
intervene in the Congo (Brazzaville) crisis because of a slow
response in assembling and deploying a peacekeeping force and a
refusal by the principal parties to respond favourably to the
call for a ceasefire. 
