Province is providing a social welfare system to guarantee a
subsistence level for most of its people, including its rural
residents.
</P>
<P>
The system covers most of the 142 cities, prefectures and
counties in Guangdong Province. According to the statistics, local
governments at various levels have allocated more than 80 million
yuan (about 9.6 million U.S. dollars) to provide subsistence aid.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's social welfare network provides support for the
elderly and other needy residents through 564 community service
centers, 9,736 shops, 1,817 homes for the aged and 146 welfare
houses.
</P>
<P>
The system works very well and plays an active role in solving
the problems of many people, according to a government official.
</P>
<P>
The province also has arranged jobs for demobilized officers
and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have collected 720 million yuan in donations
to assist poor people and provide relief in case of natural
disasters.  
