<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Cause Big Losses in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe lost more than 100
million Zimbabwe Dollars (about 10 million U.S. dollars) in
39,000 road accidents reported throughout the country last year,
The Herald daily paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Up to 1,205 people were killed and another 18,070 were injured
in the accidents.
</P>
<P>
It is vital to note that it is not only life that was lost in
an accident, but thousands of dollars which could be channelled
to development programs, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Augustine Maminimini, promotion officer of the Zimbabwe
Traffic Safety Board, told the paper that most of the accidents
last year involved light motor vehicles and buses.
</P>
<P>
He said accidents were caused by a number of factors, adding
that the main cause was human error.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown of the causes of last year's crashes showed that
inattention and poor judgment by drivers resulted in 5,188
accidents. Speeding caused up to 4,549 accidents and more than
3,060 accidents were due to failure by drivers to give way at
intersections, Maminimini added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
