<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Intercepts Fuel Supplies to Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy Tuesday
intercepted two boats transporting fuel supplies for the rebels of
the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) at sea off Kalpitiya
on the northwest coast, security sources said today.
</P>
<P>
They said the boats were intercepted after a chase and 12
barrels containing more than 500 liters of fuel and some gas
cylinders were captured.
</P>
<P>
The Navy also arrested seven Sinhalese fishermen on board the
boats and handed them over to police for interrogation.
</P>
<P>
Naval surveillance has been stepped up in the area following
information that the LTTE were getting fuel and gas supplies from
fishermen who were under the guise of fishing in these waters, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year-long ethnic war for a
separate state of their own in the north and east of the country.
 
</P>
