<HEADLINE> C and W Group of China Targets Hi-Tech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Beijing C&AMP;W Electronics Group
Co. Ltd (C&AMP;W) was set up earlier this month, aiming to become
an important base for electronics and information technology in
China, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Formerly known as Beijing Wire Communication Plant, the
company merged with a Beijing eletroplating plant and then got
goverment approval to establish the large corporate group.
</P>
<P>
Last year, C&AMP;W reported 2.7 billion yuan (325 million US
dollars) in sales, with its products ranging from
program-controled exchanges, computer dispatchers, to power supply
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The company also engages in the development and production of
wireless telecommunications products, and large screen reflecting
projection systems.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, C&AMP;W has successfully launched seven joint
ventures with Siemens of Germany, Ericsson of Sweden, Matsushita
of Japan, Unisys and NCR of the United States, Hong Kong's 3C and Asian
Electroplating Equipment Co, soliciting foreign funds of 80
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sales from these joint ventures amounted to 2.1 billion yuan
(253 million US dollars) in 1996, making up the lion's share of
the company's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
