<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama's Women Live Long </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Women in Panama have a
lengthy life averaging 75 years, the National Center
for Women announced today.
</P>
<P>
The study, conducted by the National Center for Women, showed
that Panama was one of the Latin American countries where women
enjoyed the longest life expectancy. It showed significant
differences between men and women in nutritional habits.
</P>
<P>
Men liked more fatty food and never dieted. Such habits might
cause a gradual deterioration in health, and premature death.
</P>
<P>
The report said:"In turn, women have a more practical view of
health and a more active lifestyle than men do."
</P>
<P>
The Labor Ministry said care of health was a fundamental factor
for living the high quality life enjoyed by Panamanian
women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
