<HEADLINE> Sampras Wins at Stuttgart Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 21 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
blew past Swede Magnus Gustafsson 6-3, 6-4 in his opening match at
the Stuttgart Open tennis on Tuesday in Stuttgart, Germany.
</P>
<P>
After a month long injury layoff, Sampras looked confident and
relaxed, needing just 73 minutes to advance to the third round.
The inflamed shoulder forced Sampras out of the Swiss indoors the
day after his victory at the Grand Slam.
</P>
<P>
The day also saw a trio of seeds lost their opening
matches. 10th seed Spaniard Alex Corretja lose to Swede Magnus
Larsson 6-2, 7-6, while his compatriot Felix Mantilla, the 14th
seed, was dispatched by German qualifier David Prinosil.
</P>
<P>
Another clay court specialist Austria's Thomas Muster, who won
the title here in 1995, went down to Paul Haarhuis of Netherlands
6-2, 6-7 (3-7), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
A semi-retired Boris Becker opened defence of his last
remaining title with a 6-2 6-4 first round win over fellow German
Marc-Kevin Goellner.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen-year-old Tommy Haas followed Becker, his Davis Cup
captain onto the court but failed to enter the next round, losing
a tense three-set battle to Britain's Tim Henman 7-5 3-6 6-4.
</P>
