<HEADLINE> Cooperatives Ordered to Buy Damaged Coffee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's National
Committee of Coffee Growers has ordered cooperatives and domestic
retail stores to purchase coffee beans that were damaged by the El
Nino climate phenomenon this summer.
</P>
<P>
Monday's order is intended to sell off at least 500,000 sacks
of coffee that were damaged or partially burned by the sun, head
of the National Federation of Coffee Growers Jorge Cardenas
Gutierrez said.
</P>
<P>
Commercial coffee companies have refused to buy the ravaged
coffee, but the federation said the coffee is still good for
consumption.
</P>
<P>
The measure is aimed at reducing coffee growers' losses,
Gutierrez said.
</P>
<P>
The coffee beans will be sold in the domestic market. 
</P>
