<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Standards for Amusement Park Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China has established a
national standard to ensure the safety and service quality of its
booming amusement park industry.
</P>
<P>
According to the standards which became effective on Oct. 1,
the purchase, repair and use of all facilities in the amusement
parks should meet state stipulations. A quality certificate issued
by State technical departments is required for the parks'
operation.
</P>
<P>
The standards, formulated by the National Tourism
Administration and announced by the State Technology Supervision
Administration, also spell out requirements on entertainment
venues, booking offices, catering operations and shopping centers.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, amusement parks have been mushrooming in
China because of the growing public demand," a tourism official
said. "However, lack of a unified standard has caused differences
in safety and service qualities creating potential hazards."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
