<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prices of Ecuadoran Oil Go Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Prices of Ecuadoran oil in the
international markets rose to 14, 15 and 16 dollars per barrel over
the last two weeks, the state-owned company Petroecuador said
today.
</P>
<P>
Petroecuador said at a study the best price achieved was 16
dollars per barrel by September 30. Since then, the price has
located at 16.042 dollars.
</P>
<P>
That price was for the west coast of the United States, the
first exportation target for Ecuador's oil.
</P>
<P>
As to U.S. east coast, prices kept in 16 and 17 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran oil reached its highest price of the year on
October 6, when it hit 17.599 dollars per barrel of raw oil.
</P>
<P>
Petroecuador authorities are optimistic that surges will keep
for a long term, saying oil prices may not vary much for the
second half of the year due to an expected irregular demand from
developed countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
