<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 killed in Costa Rica Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 21 (Xinhua) -- A Cessna plane crashed Monday
night in Costa Rica, killing all six people on board including
five Danish citizens, the civil air authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The five Danish were identified as Godan, Len and Ana
Soperlund, Steven Sundsprun and Lois Fourcqape and the Nicaraguan
pilot`s name is Efraim Buitrago.
</P>
<P>
The plane was making a one-hour flight between Managua and San
Jose.
</P>
<P>
The pilot radioed in the evening to San Jose's airport control
tower saying one of the engines had problems, but a few minutes
later, the control tower lost contact with the plane.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred near the Platanar volcano, 80 kilometers
from San Jose`s airport, where the plane was about to land.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said there was bad weather at the time of the
accident.
</P>
<P>
Four rescue teams, supported by a helicopter, left San Jose
for the crash spot, where the wreckage and the carbonized
bodies of the six people were found, Costa Rica's air
authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
