<HEADLINE> Tourist Highway Renovated in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Renovation work has been
completed on a grade-A highway linking Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi
province, with major tourist attractions in Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
The renovation work includes construction of dividers separating
cars from pedestrians, footbridges and overpasses on the
34-kilometer-long highway from Xi'an to Sanyuan.
</P>
<P>
The renovation has increased the speed of cars on the
highway to 80-100 kilometers per hour from 40 kph.
</P>
<P>
The renovation was made by using a World Bank loan of 120
million yuan (14.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The road is a major passage to the Xianyang International
Airport, the Mausoleum of the Yellow Emperor -- the legendary
founder of the Chinese nation -- and the northern parts of Shaanxi
Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
