<HEADLINE> Injuries Force Top Seeds Out of Luxembourg Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Irina Spirlea of
Romania and Julie Halard-Decugis of France were forced to pull out
their first round matches due to back and abdominal injuries
respectively at the Luxembourg tennis championships on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Natasha Zvereva of Belarus also retired because of
a sore shoulder after just six games of her match against
Slovakian Henrieta Nagyova.
</P>
<P>
German Barbara Rittner appeared en route to an upset against
seventh seed Kimberly Po of the United States when she took the
first set 6-0.
</P>
<P>
But Rittner was hampered by tendinitis in her right arm and
retired at 4-1 down in the final set after losing the second 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Dutchwoman Miriam Oremans posted an easy 6-1 6-3 victory over
host player Anne Kremer in a match between two wild card players
which must have left organizers with mixed feelings.
</P>
<P>
They had been forced to turn down a late request by Czech world
number two Jana Novotna as the wild cards had already been handed
out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
