<HEADLINE> Major News Items In Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister John Howard yesterday succumbed to backbench
pressure and community confusion over nursing home policy,
agreeing to consider imposing a cap on upfront fees.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
<P>
-- Economic confidence in Australia's main export outlets in
Asia slipped further yesterday after the Japanese government
disappointed markets with its latest economic reform plan.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- An Australian warship seized two foreign fishing trawlers in
a dramatic sub-Antarctic operation to curb a booming illegal trade
in patagonian toothfish.  
</P>
