<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Credit for Ghana's Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a credit of some 35 million U.S. dollars equivalent to
Ghana's health sector program support project.
</P>
<P>
The project will improve the health and nutrition of Ghanaians,
particularly the poor, through a health reform program.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to improve access, quality and
efficiency of primary health service, strengthen and reorient
service delivery to support primary health services and develop a
program to train adequate numbers of new health teams.
</P>
<P>
It is also aimed to strengthen national support systems for
human resources, logistics and supplies, financial management and
health information, as well as promote private sector involvement
in the delivery of health services.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending arm for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
