<HEADLINE> Nigerian Head of State Visits Gambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian head of state, General
Sani Abacha today paid a one-day official visit to Gambia, the
official News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said Abacha was received at the Banul airport by
Gambia President Yahya Jammeh. The two leaders then went straight
into talks.
</P>
<P>
A large delegation was accompanying Abacha on his visit,
including Nigeria's Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Gambia officials were quoted as saying that the two leaders
would talk on bilateral issues as well as the crisis in Sierra
Leone.
</P>
<P>
Abacha's visit to Gambia came a day before the expected talks
between the Sierra Leonean military regime and the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS) in Conakry, capital of
Guinea.
</P>
<P>
As Abacha is the current chairman of the ECOWAS, Nigeria is
also playing a major role in the sub-regional effort to restore
the elected government of President Ahemd Tejan Kabbah, who was
overthrown in the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow's talk would be the second between Freetown and
ECOWAS. The first broke down in July after Major Johnny Kromah
announced that his regime is ready to quit before the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the ECOWAS has imposed sanctions on Freetown and
succeeded in convincing the United Nations to do the same.
</P>
</TEXT>
