<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister Meets Hong Kong Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair Tuesday met with Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of China's
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders had a "useful and cordial" conversation on a
wide range of subjects that are interested by both Hong Kong and
Britain, Tung told reporters after 40-minute meeting. But no
details were available.
</P>
